    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've prepared:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add Model Rename Feature\n\n**4 files to modify**, all following existing patterns with no new imports required:\n\n### `api/types.go`\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct with `Source`/`Destination` string fields — mirrors `CopyRequest` exactly.\n\n### `api/client.go`\nAdd `Client.Rename(ctx, *RenameRequest) error` calling `c.do(..., http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", ...)` — mirrors `Client.Copy()`.\n\n### `server/routes.go` (2 changes)\n1. **`RenameHandler` method** inserted after `CopyHandler` (~line 1483):\n   - Parses JSON body, validates non-empty fields → 400\n   - Validates both names via `model.ParseName()` + `IsValid()` → 400 `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n   - Checks destination doesn't exist: `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → 409 Conflict if found\n   - Resolves source: `getExistingName(src)` → 404 if not found\n   - Copies: `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404/500 on failure\n   - Deletes source: `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` → 500 on failure\n   - Returns `{\"status\": \"success\"}` 200 on success\n2. **Route registration** `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after `/api/copy` line (~1698)\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` (3 changes)\n1. `RenameHandler` func after `CopyHandler` — calls `client.Rename()`, prints `Renamed \"X\" to \"Y\"`\n2. `renameCmd` cobra command after `copyCmd` — `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`\n3. `renameCmd` registered in `rootCmd.AddCommand(...)` after `copyCmd`",
